public class PropertyMap extends com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.map.VariableMap<String>
A property map is a VariableMap with strings as both keys and values.

Creating and Loading Property Maps

A property map can be created or loaded from a Resource with:

  • propertyMap() - Creates an empty property map
  • propertyMap(VariableMap) - Creates a property map from the given variable map
  • loadPropertyMap(Listener, Resource) - Loads a property map from the given resource
  • loadPropertyMap(Listener, InputStream) - Loads property map from the given input stream
  • loadPropertyMap(Listener, ResourceFolder, String) - Loads property map from the given package path and relative path
  • loadLocalizedPropertyMap(Listener, PackagePath, Locale, LocaleLanguage)

Access

  • get(String, StringConverter)
  • get(String, StringConverter, Object)

Conversions

  • copy() - A copy of this property map using ObjectPopulator
  • BaseStringMap.asLong(String) - The given value as a long
  • BaseStringMap.asDouble(String) - The given value as a double
  • BaseStringMap.asCount(String) - The given value as a Count
  • asFile(String)
  • asFolder(String)
  • asJson()

Adding to Property Maps

In addition to the methods inherited from VariableMap, property maps add the following methods:

  • comment(String, String) - Attaches the given comment to the given key
  • addProperties(Object, PropertyFilter) - Adds the properties of the given object that match the filter to this map

Saving

  • save(WritableResource) - Saves this property map to the given resource
  • save(WritableResource, String) - Saves this property map to the given resource with the given heading

Expansion

  • expanded()
  • expandedWith(VariableMap)
